018/**
019 * DTO for an HTML <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/tabular-data.html#the-th-element">&lt;th&gt;</a>
020 * element.
021 *
022 * <p>
023 * The th element represents a header cell in a table. It is used to contain header information
024 * for a column or row, providing context and meaning to the data cells (td) in the table. The th
025 * element supports various attributes for accessibility, spanning multiple columns or rows, and
026 * defining the relationship between header and data cells.
027 *
028 * <h5 class='section'>Examples:</h5>
029 * <p class='bcode w800'>
030 *    <jk>import static</jk> org.apache.juneau.bean.html5.HtmlBuilder.*;
031 * 
032 *    <jc>// Simple header cell</jc>
033 *    Th <jv>simple</jv> = <jsm>th</jsm>(<js>"Name"</js>);
034 * 
035 *    <jc>// Header cell with scope</jc>
036 *    Th <jv>scoped</jv> = <jsm>th</jsm>(<js>"Age"</js>)
037 *       .scope(<js>"col"</js>);
038 * 
039 *    <jc>// Header cell spanning multiple columns</jc>
040 *    Th <jv>colspan</jv> = <jsm>th</jsm>(<js>"Contact Information"</js>)
041 *       .colspan(2);
042 * 
043 *    <jc>// Header cell with abbreviation</jc>
044 *    Th <jv>abbreviated</jv> = <jsm>th</jsm>(<js>"Quantity"</js>)
045 *       .abbr(<js>"Qty"</js>);
046 * 
047 *    <jc>// Header cell with sorting</jc>
048 *    Th <jv>sorted</jv> = <jsm>th</jsm>(<js>"Price"</js>)
049 *       .sorted(<js>"asc"</js>);
050 * 
051 *    <jc>// Header cell with styling</jc>
052 *    Th <jv>styled</jv> = <jsm>th</jsm>(<js>"Status"</js>)
053 *       ._class(<js>"header-cell"</js>);
054 * 
055 *    <jc>// Header cell with complex content</jc>
056 *    Th <jv>complex</jv> = <jsm>th</jsm>(
057 *       .children(
058 *          new Strong().children("Total"),
059 *          " ",
060 *          new Small().children("(USD)")
061 *       );
062 * </p>
063 *
064 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
065 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanHtml5">juneau-bean-html5</a>
066 * </ul>
067 */
068@Bean(typeName="th")
069@FluentSetters
070public class Th extends HtmlElementMixed {
071
072   /**
073    * Creates an empty {@link Th} element.
074    */
075   public Th() {}
076
077   /**
078    * Creates a {@link Th} element with the specified child nodes.
079    *
080    * @param children The child nodes.
081    */
082   public Th(Object...children) {
083      children(children);
084   }
085
086   /**
087    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/tabular-data.html#attr-th-abbr">abbr</a> attribute.
088    *
089    * <p>
090    * Specifies an alternative, abbreviated label for the header cell. This is used by screen readers
091    * and other assistive technologies when referencing the cell in other contexts.
092    *
093    * <p>
094    * The abbreviation should be shorter than the full header text but still meaningful.
095    *
096    * @param abbr The abbreviated label for the header cell.
097    * @return This object.
098    */
099   public Th abbr(String value) {
100      attr("abbr", value);
101      return this;
102   }
103
104   /**
105    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/tabular-data.html#attr-tdth-colspan">colspan</a> attribute.
106    *
107    * <p>
108    * Number of columns that the cell is to span.
109    *
110    * @param colspan
111    *    The new value for this attribute.
112    *    Typically a {@link Number} or {@link String}.
113    * @return This object.
114    */
115   public Th colspan(Object value) {
116      attr("colspan", value);
117      return this;
118   }
119
120   /**
121    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/tabular-data.html#attr-tdth-headers">headers</a> attribute.
122    *
123    * <p>
124    * Specifies the IDs of header cells that apply to this table cell. This creates a programmatic
125    * relationship between the cell and its headers for accessibility purposes.
126    *
127    * <p>
128    * Multiple IDs can be specified as a space-separated list.
129    *
130    * @param headers The IDs of header cells that apply to this cell.
131    * @return This object.
132    */
133   public Th headers(String value) {
134      attr("headers", value);
135      return this;
136   }
137
138   /**
139    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/tabular-data.html#attr-tdth-rowspan">rowspan</a> attribute.
140    *
141    * <p>
142    * Number of rows that the cell is to span.
143    *
144    * @param rowspan
145    *    The new value for this attribute.
146    *    Typically a {@link Number} or {@link String}.
147    * @return This object.
148    */
149   public Th rowspan(Object value) {
150      attr("rowspan", value);
151      return this;
152   }
153
154   /**
155    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/tabular-data.html#attr-th-scope">scope</a> attribute.
156    *
157    * <p>
158    * Specifies which cells the header cell applies to. This helps define the relationship
159    * between header and data cells for accessibility.
160    *
161    * <p>
162    * Possible values:
163    * <ul>
164    *    <li><js>"row"</js> - Header applies to all cells in the same row</li>
165    *    <li><js>"col"</js> - Header applies to all cells in the same column</li>
166    *    <li><js>"rowgroup"</js> - Header applies to all cells in the same row group</li>
167    *    <li><js>"colgroup"</js> - Header applies to all cells in the same column group</li>
168    * </ul>
169    *
170    * @param scope Which cells the header cell applies to.
171    * @return This object.
172    */
173   public Th scope(String value) {
174      attr("scope", value);
175      return this;
176   }
177
178   /**
179    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/tabular-data.html#attr-th-sorted">sorted</a> attribute.
180    *
181    * <p>
182    * Specifies the sort direction and ordinality of the column. This indicates how the table
183    * is currently sorted and which column is the primary sort key.
184    *
185    * <p>
186    * Common values:
187    * <ul>
188    *    <li><js>"asc"</js> - Column is sorted in ascending order</li>
189    *    <li><js>"desc"</js> - Column is sorted in descending order</li>
190    *    <li><js>"asc 1"</js> - Column is the primary sort key in ascending order</li>
191    *    <li><js>"desc 1"</js> - Column is the primary sort key in descending order</li>
192    * </ul>
193    *
194    * @param sorted The sort direction and ordinality of the column.
195    * @return This object.
196    */
197   public Th sorted(String value) {
198      attr("sorted", value);
199      return this;
200   }
